President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring June 2017 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. The proclamation pays tribute to the contributions African Americans have made and continue to make to American music. It highlights the indelible legacy of musicians who have witnessed the nation's greatest achievements and injustices, and how their creativity has shaped every genre of music. The proclamation also recognizes the centennial birthdays of jazz musicians Dizzy Gillespie and Ella Fitzgerald. It calls upon public officials, educators, and all Americans to observe the month with activities and programs that raise awareness and appreciation of African-American music.